# | JAVA | Step by step Solution -->
1. We wil create a matrix call `res` with dimensions (`m`,`n`). When created, the matrix will contain only zeros.
    Zeros represent unguarded cells.

2. We add the walls to the correct positions in `res`, the same case for the guards. 
    Walls will be represented in `res` with the number 2 and guards using the number 1.

3. We start parsing the matrix, if we find a 1 (guard), we try to change the respective cells 
    affected in `res` with the number 3 until we face a wall or another guard.

4. Once all the guards have guarded their respective cells, we parse the matrix again, if we find
    a zero (unguarded cell) we add one to the counter (`result`).

5. We return `result` :). Hope you have understand it!! 

